properties.name: Grew up here
properties.description: Posted by Imovane Good area to have kids 25 years ago. Quiet safe friendly and close to the lake. Went back last year. Ever heard the phrase you can\'t go back home? It was sad.

properties.name: Neceopolis
properties.description: Posted by Imovane One of the quainest, most quiet and beautiful cemetaries I\'ve seen. William Lyon McKenzie lies here as well as Father of Confederation George Brown. Many important people in early York and then Toronto in 1841. Visit the chapel, astounding. Victorian Revival architecture.

properties.name: Redevelopment
properties.description: Posted by Imovane This corner needs serious Redevelopment quickly. New Popeye\'s fast food going in SE corner and Kormanhouse lofts going on SW corner. Slowly it is changing.

properties.name: Tim Hortons
properties.description: Posted by Imovane 549 parliament st. toronto,onThis is the most beautiful Tim Hortons in the city. Exposed brick, copper decorative ceilings, very Victorian. Plus historical shots of the immediate area c. Early 1900\'s. Usually busy, and very busy on weekends. It\'s Tim Hortons.

properties.name: Umbra
properties.description: Posted by Imovane The new Umbra store on Queen West just north of CITY TV building. Very nice stuff but it\'s not bargin bin pricing. But trendy, minimalist design is your thing, this is what you want to check out. 5471054710

properties.name: Up Country
properties.description: Posted by Imovane 95 berkeley street torontoBeautiful furniture. Were going out of business but something apparently saved them. I think the store is even larger. Nice gay guys in the store, pretty cool guys.
